# Where files go

Follow **`docs/policy/repository-layout-policy.md`** for full rules. Summary:

| Kind | Location |
|------|-----------|
| Library / runtime Python | `metacompressor/` only (`src/` equivalent in this repo) |
| Pytest (`test_*.py`) | `metacompressor/tests/` (`tests/` equivalent) |
| Slow benchmarks, acceptance drivers | `benchmarks/` → reports under `results/<domain>/` (see `results/README.md`; stale snapshots → `archive/`) |
| Policies, ADRs, architecture prose | `docs/` — **`docs/policy/`**, **`docs/planning/`**, **`docs/differential/`**, **`docs/adr/`** (see **`docs/README.md`**) |
| CI/repo maintenance scripts | `scripts/` (not imported by `metacompressor`) |
| Cursor rules / skills / commands / subagents | `.cursor/rules`, `.cursor/skills`, `.cursor/commands`, `.cursor/agents` |
| Workspace editor defaults | `.vscode/` |
| Local scratch / CLI test dumps | `tmp/scripts/`, `tmp/logs/`, `mc_test_output/` (gitignored) — never as sole spec |

Do not add production logic under `benchmarks/` or `results/`. Do not commit large generated blobs without team agreement; prefer regenerating from `benchmarks/`. If report sprawl grows, quarantine stale artifacts into `archive/`.

Before creating a file, pick the row above; if none fit, extend **`docs/policy/repository-layout-policy.md`** in the same PR.
